The paper deals with the problem of private data disclosure, which is a topic in information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves linear programming and optimization, which are topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the correlation between random variables, which is a topic in cs.MM (Multimedia).
